                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 W 451/136: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 14, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. Your 455, November 13, 1 p.m. I have consulted the President, who agrees
                    with you that it would be helpful to discuss recent developments. Inasmuch as
                    the President will arrive in Warm Springs on Saturday afternoon, he suggests
                    that you come to see him there on Sunday.<note n="66" xml:id="d495fn66">November
                        19.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
